  "texts": [
    "• Irrelevant Focus: Studies that did not focus on LLMs or their applications in education were excluded to maintain relevance to the research questions.• Lack of Empirical Analysis: Studies without empirical results, such as theoretical discussions or opinion pieces, were excluded to prioritize measurable insights.",
    "• Absence of Performance Evaluation: Studies that failed to evaluate the performance or effectiveness of LLMs in education were excluded to ensure the findings contribute to actionable insights.",
    "Justification for criteriaThe inclusion and exclusion criteria were designed to ensure that the selected studies:• Provide evidence-based insights relevant to the application of LLMs in education.• Align with the study's focus on practical, empirical findings rather than theoretical or speculative discussions.• Reflect recent developments and emerging trends, ensuring the review's relevance and significance.",
    "Quality assessmentThe selected studies were further evaluated using the Modified CASP Checklist to assess their methodological rigor and relevance.",
    "Table 5 illustrates the quality assessment criteria, focusing on critical aspects such as clarity of objectives, relevance to LLM applications in education, and empirical robustness."
